column1: # all of the data from the original excel file was copied into here so I could easily make new columns for each category of relevant data. For "white disc egg sacs" I counted them as one, even if they had multiple eggs inside. Code of "LT" denotes only that this column of data comes from the "leaf tie" data set, which may include arthropods other than leaf tiers.  There are currently WAY too many categories than there should be. I also altered the category name for "Treatments" to match my "Wind Exposure" column for my visual survey of arthropods. Made leaf damage categories for LMF (leaf middle fold), LER (leaf edge roll) and LB (leaf bundle, various types included) in order to compare abundance/damage across years.
